headlines.description: Ray Spalding had 19 points and a career-high 13 rebounds before leaving midway through the second half with an injury, Deng Adel and Jordan Nwora each made a key 3-pointer late and No. 19 Louisville held off Saint Francis 84-72 on Friday night.

video.headline: Spalding pushes Louisville past Saint Francis

headlines.description: Devin Sibley opened the second half with a pair of free throws, a 3-pointer, a steal and dunk and another 3, Furman scored the first 11 points after halftime, stretched a five-point lead to 29 and held off New Hampshire, 78-64 in Friday's opener of...
headlines.shortLinkText: Sibley ignites Furman in 2nd half, Paladins roll, 78-64

headlines.description: Joshua Filmore, in his second game back from a serious knee injury, scored 19 points, including a pair of key free throws with 10 seconds left as Southeastern Louisiana edged Samford 77-71 on Friday in the Savannah Invitational.
headlines.shortLinkText: Filmore scores 19 with 2 clutch FTs, SE Louisiana wins 77-71

headlines.description: Jalone Friday scored half of his 14 points in overtime, including the go-ahead 3-pointer with 12.9 seconds to play, and Abilene Christian edged Campbell 85-80 in overtime on Friday at the Creek Classic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Friday leads Abilene Christian past Campbell 85-80 in OT

headlines.description: Jairus Lyles made two free throws with 12.6 seconds left and Maryland, Baltimore County held off Nicholls State 89-88 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lyles hits late go-ahead FTs, UMBC tops Nicholls St 89-88

headlines.description: For the second time in as many games, Devin Harris set a career-high with 24 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and Jacksonville held off Fairfield 92-84 in a Wright State Tournament game on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jacksonville dumps Fairfield 92-84 behind Harris' 24 PTs

headlines.description: Dylan Frye and Rodrick Caldwell each hit five 3-pointers and Demajeo Wiggins scored 20 points with 12 rebounds as Bowling Green defeated South Carolina Upstate 83-74 Friday in the Creek Classic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Caldwell, Frye and Wiggins lead Bowling Green to 83-74 win

headlines.description: Koby Thomas displayed a near-perfect shooting touch going nine of 10 from the floor, making three of four 3-pointers along the way, and finishing with 21 points as Robert Morris defeated Norfolk State 75-53 Friday for its second straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Robert Morris tops Norfolk St. 75-53 for 2nd straight win

headlines.description: Keaton Wallace scored 14 points, George Willborn II had 12 and Texas-San Antonio defeated Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 72-58 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UTSA uses big start to turn back A&M-CC 72-58

headlines.description: Khalil Ahmad scored 25 points and Kyle Allman chipped in 13 points and Cal State Fullerton beat Sacramento State 68-63 Friday on the second day of the Wooden Legacy.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cal St. Fullerton takes down Sacramento St. 68-63

headlines.description: Isaiah Reese scored seven of his 16 points during a 12-0 fourth-quarter run and Canisius turned back Texas State 68-62 at the Men Against Breast Cancer Showcase.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reese sparks late run, leads Canisius over Texas State 68-62

headlines.description: Justin Davis buried a 3-pointer with two seconds left in the game and Cal State Bakersfield rallied for a 64-62 victory over Idaho on Friday night at the Great Alaska Shootout.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late 3-pointer lifts CSU Bakersfield over Idaho 64-62

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
